Since 2018, IWC has been licensed to work on watches for the entire U.S. Navy and Marine Corps aviation units, including Blue Angels® and the 247 active and 100 inactive squadrons.
Strike Fighter Squadron 27, known as the “Royal Maces”, is stationed at Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni in Japan and forms part of Carrier Air Wing 5. The Pilot’s Watch Chronograph Edition “Royal Maces” (Ref. IW389107) features a black zirconium oxide ceramic case. The pushers and the crown are made of Ceratanium®. The dial features the “Maces” patch and a yellow day-date indication. The yellow is the signature “Maces” colour. The case back is made of grade 5 titanium and features an engraving of the squadron’s F/A-18E Super Hornet jet next to the official squadron denomination “VFA-27”. #IWCPilot

IW389108) has a case made of black zirconium oxide ceramic with its pushers and the crown in Ceratanium®. The squadron’s patch with the classic top hat can be found at 6 o’clock on the dial and engraved on the titanium case back. The day-date display, the tip of the chronograph seconds hand, the small seconds and the stitching on the black calfskin strap add more details in the squadron’s characteristic red. #IWCPilot

Teamwork. Professionalism. Precision. This is the motto of the “Blue Angels®” U.S. Navy Flight Demonstration Squadron. The Pilot’s Watch Chronograph Edition “Blue Angels®” (Ref. IW389109) is inspired by the military exclusive watch developed with Blue Angels members in Pensacola, featuring a blue ceramic case. The chronograph pushers and the crown are made of IWC-developed Ceratanium®. The iconic “Blue Angels®” crest is at 6 o’clock on the dial; the characteristic lettering is engraved on the titanium case back. Yellow details are provided by the chronograph seconds hand, the small seconds and the day-date display at 3 o’clock. This watch is fitted with a blue rubber strap with textile inlay. #IWCPilot

“Sport has the power to change the world”. Since 2006, IWC has issued a special edition timepiece in honour of Laureus Sport for Good each year. The work of Laureus Sport for Good follows this powerful guiding principle established by Nelson Mandela. Currently, the foundation supports over 250 programmes in more than 50 countries worldwide, using sport to transform the lives of children and young people and end violence, discrimination, and disadvantage. 

The Pilot’s Watch Automatic Edition “Laureus Sport for Good” features the manufacture calibre 32111 boasting a power reserve of 120h. The printed dial roots back to the early days of aviation watches and is in line with IWC’s utilitarian Pilot’s Watch design. This timepiece is launched in collaboration with the Laureus Sport for Good Foundation supporting sports-based community programs all over the world and it is limited to only 750 pieces worldwide.
